Thanks, John.<br><br>
Spatz what is your purpose here? That I should openly engage Cook? I have, and he actually admits that some of my opinions made him think. Not change his mind, but he thinks. Unlike you I am not interested in *BEING RIGHT* I am not interested in *WINNING* either. I have always considered myself a winner, and have never accepted the stereotypes that have befallen returning vets of our era. Forget the divide and conquer bullshit! <br><br>
The lack of acceptance by the citizens of this country never made me lose sight of my accomplishments. <br><br>
In June of 1970 I was awarded the Silver Star. The other men in my platoon received Bronze Stars with V devices. I am most proud of the men I led. Many on this channel are leaders of men this very day. Back in my early days, leaders were stigmatized. Not anymore. The real leaders of this country are stepping forward, with or without recognition. They are Vietnam Veterans. Our purpose and our sense of mission is undaunted by any detractors. So get out of the way spatz. <br><br>
Our mission is not to provide &quot;why's and what for's&quot; to people whose greatest desires are to be proven *RIGHT* by history. Our mission is to rebuild this country - and the means lie within all of us who served in Vietnam. Some haven't realized it yet. Our mission didn't end in Vietnam.<br><br>
I have another friend who protested the war. Born into wealth, he renounces it every day by being a carpenter who wears overalls and gets his hands dirty. He is as fine of a craftsman as can be found anywhere. He is one of the rare breed whose word is his bond. Rare indeed. We talk about the war on occasion. Never has he felt as if he was the one being shortchanged. He shows his admiration and respect for veterans by showing my Vietnam War stories (which another friend downloaded for him) to people he knows. It would be beneath him to request a memorial for protesting. He asks nor demands nothing. One of the most tactful men I know. Humility, spatz. Humility.<br><br>
You show your lack of a sense of justice by accusing others of lying, while at the same time, refusing to provide EVIDENCE. I posted a week ago that I knew a Marine who had talked with Cook, and said that Cook had been at Liberty Bridge. I even offered to give the url of the man's website, to anyone, back channel. If you were so intent on proving Cook to be a fake why didn't you take me up on the proposal? Cook, himself, told you where you might reference his background. If I were the accuser, I would make damned sure I had valid information.<br><br>
Come off it spatz. You really are just a young feller who, possibly, had an older brother who was a war protestor, right? I know many who protested, none are like you. How come?<br>

